\section{Model Overview}{


The LPPLS model assumes that financial bubbles are characterized by:
\itemize{
\item Super-exponential price growth (power law with exponent m < 1)
\item Log-periodic oscillations with increasing frequency
\item A finite-time singularity at the critical time tc
}

The model equation is:
\deqn{E[ln p(t)] = A + B|t_c - t|^m + C|t_c - t|^m \cos[\omega \ln|t_c - t| - \phi]}

Where:
\itemize{
\item A: Log price at critical time
\item B: Amplitude of power law growth
\item C: Amplitude of log-periodic oscillations
\item m: Power law exponent (0 < m < 1)
\item ω: Log-periodic frequency
\item tc: Critical time
\item φ: Phase parameter
}
}

